The paper deals with signal processing and optimization techniques to solve the phaseless super-resolution problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves sparse signal recovery, which falls under cs.SP (Signal Processing). The proposed method involves Semidefinite Programming, which is a common optimization technique used in cs.SI (Systems and Control). The paper also deals with image super-resolution, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which is a common theme in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
